Build-Depends:
 debhelper-compat (= 13),
 libsqlite3-dev
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: batrun
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: systemd, udev
Description: battery intelligence, zero batshit
 batrun records battery state on suspend, resume, boot, shutdown and
 AC plug/unplug events into a local SQLite database so it can later
 report realistic single-charge runtime derived from your actual usage
 instead of the firmware's optimistic guess.
 .
 The recorder is invoked from hooks (systemd-sleep, a systemd oneshot
 service, and a udev rule) so nothing runs between events.
